court on the
left that Elizabeth Wydra
described.

36:34.626 --> 36:38.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The other thing is, you just --
it changes
when you're a judge and you
become a justice.

36:38.630 --> 36:42.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You get freed from a lot of the
constraints
of existing precedent.

36:42.100 --> 36:46.237 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So nobody ought to say with
great confidence
what any of these judges will do
when they're

