40:31.729 --> 40:33.164 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Good to have you with us, Mr.
Cabrera.

40:33.264 --> 40:34.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANGEL CABRERA, President, George
Mason University:
Thank you for having me.

40:35.066 --> 40:37.735 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: First of all,
let's talk about
your perspective as an immigrant
yourself,

40:37.835 --> 40:43.508 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
having seen the university
system here from
Spain, and now on the inside.

40:43.608 --> 40:46.511 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm curious how that affects
your perspective
on this whole issue.

40:46.611 --> 40:52.317 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANGEL CABRERA: Well, first of
all, the American
universities have a tremendous
advantage around

40:52.417 --> 40:57.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the world, because they're the
number one
place where students from all
over the world

40:57.388 --> 40:58.289 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
want to study.

40:58.389 --> 41:00.224 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I was there myself.

41:00.325 --> 41:05.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I graduated from college from
Madrid, Spain,
and my dream was to come to one
of the great

41:05.530 --> 41:07.332 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
American research universities.

41:07.432 --> 41:10.702 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And like that, there are
thousands, hundreds
of thousands of students from
around the world

41:10.802 --> 41:12.570 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
every year.

41:12.670 --> 41:14.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: And the higher
education system
here really does remain a
magnet, doesn't

41:14.906 --> 41:15.807 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
it?

41:15.907 --> 41:17.842 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ANGEL CABRERA: Absolutely.

41:17.942 --> 41:21.279 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And not only that gives the
American university
a great advantage, but it gives
an advantage,

41:21.379 --> 41:23.147 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
also, to the American economy.

41:23.247 --> 41:27.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, when you do the numbers
and look at,
for example, out of the recent
start-ups,

41:27.585 --> 41:33.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
