medicine
and physiology or physics, about
40 percent

45:39.170 --> 45:40.371 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
were born outside of the United
States.

45:40.471 --> 45:42.707 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So our science is tied to
immigration.

45:42.807 --> 45:45.176 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Our entrepreneurship is tied to
immigration.

45:45.276 --> 45:47.345 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Our innovation is tied to
immigration.

45:47.445 --> 45:51.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Angel Cabrera,
president of
George Mason University, thank
you for your

45:51.182 --> 45:52.083 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
time.

45:52.183 --> 45:53.084 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ANGEL CABRERA: You're welcome.

45:53.184 --> 45:56.821 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thank you for having me.

45:56.921 --> 46:09.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now we look at
efforts to change
the face of classical music, and
shake up

46:09.200 --> 46:12.470 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
tradition while keeping true to
the sound.

46:12.570 --> 46:14.405 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown is our guide.

46:14.505 --> 46:20.144 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: An orchestra
performing with
singers.

46:20.244 --> 46:22.046 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
See anything unusual?

46:22.146 --> 46:29.320 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At a recent concert by the
Dallas Opera, the
focus was on the conductors,
women conductors.

46:29.420 --> 46:37.194 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And in the still highly
traditional world
of classical music, that is
unusual.

46:37.294 --> 46:46.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This was the culmination of the
second annual
Hart Institute for Women
Conductors, six women

46:46.737 --> 46:53.344 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and four observers, chosen from
156 applicants
around the world, taking part in
an intensive

46:53.444 --> 46:59.216 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
two-week rehearsal workshop,
combined with
sessions on how to build and
maintain a career.

46:59.316 --> 47:01.786 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KEITH CERNY, General Director,
Dallas Opera:
I have absolutely seen very
talented women

47:01.886 --> 47:04.622 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who are held back from where
they ought to
be.

47:04.722 --> 47:08.392 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: It's the
brainchild of Dallas
Opera general director Keith
Cerny.

47:08.492 --> 47:14.899 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KEITH CERNY: I think there are
some individuals
who are opposed to the idea of
women leaders,

47:14.999 --> 47:17.201 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
whether on the podium or running
large opera
companies.

47:17.301 --> 47:20.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Fortunately, there aren't that
many of those
people, but there's certainly
some.

47:20.871 --> 47:25.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, more generally, I think
it's an issue
where, because there's fewer
women in those

47:25.876 --> 47:30.481 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
positions, search committees and
general directors
and symphony CEOs don't tend to
think so much

47:30.581 --> 47:32.583 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about hiring women for those
opportunities.

47:32.683 --> 47:34.485 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: It's just not
part of their
thinking?

47:34.585 --> 47:36.387 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KEITH CERNY: It's just not part
of the thinking.

47:36.487 --> 47:40.791 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: According to
industry data,
of the nine largest American
opera companies

47:40.891 --> 47:46.697 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by budget, none has a female
music director
and principal conductor.

47:46.797 --> 47:54.739 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Marin Alsop in Baltimore,
who served on
the faculty at the Dallas
workshop, remains

47:54.839 --> 47:59.376 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the sole woman music director at
the nation's
24 largest orchestras.

47:59.477 --> 48:05.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Dallas, Cerny hired Nicole
Paiement as
principal guest conductor, and
she played

48:06.016 --> 48:07.752 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a large role at the institute,
encouraging.

48:07.852 --> 48:10.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICOLE PAIEMENT, Principal Guest
Conductor,
Dallas Opera: When you have an
idea, which

48:10.354 --> 48:11.655 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
are always very, very good...

48:11.756 --> 48:12.823 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Cajoling,
teaching.

48:12.923 --> 48:14.925 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NICOLE PAIEMENT: ... say one
thing and move
on.

48:15.025 --> 48:18.696 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You sort of explain it five
times, but I think
we get it the first time.

48:18.796 --> 48:23.901 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Paiement runs her
own small
opera company in San Francisco,
and travels

48:24.001 --> 48:25.803 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the world performing with
orchestras.

48:25.903 --> 48:30.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICOLE PAIEMENT: I know there is
that surprise
phenomenon every time I'm guest
conducting

48:31.041 --> 48:33.310 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for the first time.

48:33.410 --> 48:36.080 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They are surprised when I arrive
on the podium.

48:36.180 --> 48:37.081 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I don't have the physique.

48:37.181 --> 48:38.082 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I'm a woman.

48:38.182 --> 48:39.083 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm a small woman.

48:39.183 --> 48:40.084 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

48:40.184 --> 48:41.085 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
What do you mean?

48:41.185 --> 48:42.453 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You sense that the audience is
surprised?

48:42.553 --> 48:44.088 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NICOLE PAIEMENT: It's not the
audience, but
the musicians.

48:44.188 --> 48:48.492 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I arrive, I can feel that
they are like,
oh, OK, that's our conductor.

48:48.592 --> 48:50.294 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it's a little bit of a
surprise.

48:50.394 --> 48:52.062 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It can be refreshing.

48:52.163 --> 48:53.998 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But do you have
-- does that
make you have to prove yourself,
or...

48:54.098 --> 48:57.902 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NICOLE PAIEMENT: I have -- no,
not at all,
because they see what I'm doing
on the podium

48:58.002 --> 49:03.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is not there to be a leader and
to be the
boss and to be -- but to make
music as a collaborative

49:03.174 --> 49:04.542 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
art form.

49:04.642 --> 49:06.944 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And, you know, the art of
conducting has changed
a great deal.

49:07.044 --> 49:08.712 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The era of the tyrant on the
podium...

49:08.813 --> 49:09.780 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Right, that
stereotype.

49:09.880 --> 49:12.283 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NICOLE PAIEMENT: That stereotype
is long gone.

49:12.383 --> 49:18.722 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Romanian
conductor Mihaela
Cesa-Goje recalls something she
learned from

49:18.823 --> 49:20.457 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
one of her mentors.

49:20.558 --> 49:22.960 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIHAELA CESA-GOJE, Conductor:
Marin Alsop
is giving a very, very good
example.

49:23.060 --> 49:29.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, if a woman goes and conducts
with her
hand like that, everybody,
maybe, they might

49:29.934 --> 49:32.469 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
say, oh, that's such a girly
thing.

49:32.570 --> 49:35.806 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But if a man does that, he's so
sensitive.

49:35.906 --> 49:40.344 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, I think it's a lot of
question of perception,
how people are looking.

49:40.444 --> 49:47.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I try not to focus so much
on this, because
if I'm thinking about this every
day, then

49:47.117 --> 49:48.886 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
you just don't do anything.

49:48.986 --> 49:52.790 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: That was what we
heard from
others here as well, including
the youngest

49:52.890 --> 49:59.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
participant, 26-year-old Tianyi
Lu, who grew
up in New Zealand, love the
music, embrace

49:59.196 --> 50:02.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the work, and focus on how to
get better.

50:02.433 --> 50:04.869 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But they're all used to being a
outnumbered
in this world.

50:04.969 --> 50:06.637 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TIANYI LU, Conductor: It's just
a different
dynamic.

50:06.737 --> 50:10.207 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have been in master classes
where I'm the
only girl, and I think...

50:10.307 --> 50:11.308 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: And what happens?

50:11.408 --> 50:13.177 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TIANYI LU: Well, certain things
have happened.

50:13.277 --> 50:17.081 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think, for me, it's more
to do with,
sometimes, it's very easy for
everyone to

50:17.181 --> 50:21.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
pretend like they're really
confident, whereas
I don't think I'm the sort of
person who can

50:21.485 --> 50:23.420 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
pretend as well as others.

50:23.520 --> 50:27.858 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, I actually need real
confidence, and that
comes with time in front of the
orchestra,

50:27.958 --> 50:33.597 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
time with people who are
experienced giving
me their suggestions, their
support and encouragement.

50:33.697 --> 50:37.735 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And, for me, that's the
important thing.

50:37.835 --> 50:42.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Time in front of
a prestigious
ensemble is key to the
institute.

50:42.640 --> 50:45.843 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For a conductor, the orchestra
is her instrument.

50:45.943 --> 50:52.182 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rehearsals were augmented by
one-on-one sessions
with more seasoned conductors,
including Italian

50:52.283 --> 50:54.051 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
conductor Carlo Montanaro.

50:54.151 --> 50:59.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But is there something that a
conductor has
to have, you know, that you must
have to be

50:59.924 --> 51:02.059 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a good -- what makes a great
conductor?

51:02.159 --> 51:03.794 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CARLO MONTANARO, Conductor:
Charisma.

51:03.894 --> 51:05.696 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Charisma?

51:05.796 --> 51:11.602 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CARLO MONTANARO: Knowledge,
technique, being
true on the podium, not fake
yourself on the

51:11.702 --> 51:15.539 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
podium, don't make a show,
believe in the
music that you're conducting.

51:15.639 --> 51:19.410 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Do you see
differences in women
and men conductors?

51:19.510 --> 51:20.411 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CARLO MONTANARO: No, zero.

51:20.511 --> 51:21.412 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Zero.

51:21.512 --> 51:22.413 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
CARLO MONTANARO: I see a
musician.

51:22.513 --> 51:24.615 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I don't treat them women, men.

51:24.715 --> 51:26.350 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
No.

51:26.450 --> 51:30.721 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Off the podium,
there were
other very practical lessons, on
building

51:30.821 --> 51:37.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a resume and networking, whether
and how to
hire an agent, and developing
executive leadership

51:37.261 --> 51:40.431 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
skills, in order to one day move
into upper
management.

51:40.531 --> 51:42.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN: We really have to do our
homework.

51:42.466 --> 51:46.470 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We really have to educate
ourselves if we
are going to be in this field.

51:46.570 --> 51:49.640 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You will most likely be the
musical director
of an orchestra.

51:49.740 --> 51:51.842 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you will have understand
about all of
that.

51:51.942 --> 51:53.544 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You are going to have to deal
with a board.

51:53.644 --> 51:58.549 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the board is going to talk
to you about
numbers, right?

51:58.649 --> 52:04.254 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: American
Elizabeth Askren has
guest conducted in many leading
European venues

52:04.355 --> 52:08.692 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and, like the others here, is
hoping one day
to be a music director.

52:08.792 --> 52:13.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She saw the institute as a great
opportunity
for learning with and from other
women.

52:13.464 --> 52:17.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELIZABETH ASKREN, Conductor:
It's a safe space
for us to treat some of those
issues, some

52:17.167 --> 52:22.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of which are just, you know,
common, everyday
things, like questions that all
conductors

52:22.139 --> 52:23.540 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
have to face.

52:23.640 --> 52:28.112 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then there are some issues
to explore
that may pertain to women.

52:28.212 --> 52:34.952 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The fact that the numbers are
rather low in
positions of directorship in
opera, why is

52:35.052 --> 52:35.953 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
that?

52:36.053 --> 52:37.721 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Can we talk about that?

52:37.821 --> 52:40.257 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The Dallas Opera
has made a
20-year commitment to this
institute.

52:40.357 --> 52:44.428 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I asked general director Keith
Cerny how he
will judge success.

52:44.528 --> 52:48.265 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KEITH CERNY: It would be
terrific to think
that, 20 years from now, this
whole issue

52:48.365 --> 52:53.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
will have gone away, and men and
women will
be equally evaluated for
positions on the

52:53.137 --> 52:54.405 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
podium.

52:54.505 --> 52:55.906 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think that may be a little
optimistic, but
what I want...

52:56.006 --> 52:57.474 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: You do?

52:57.574 --> 52:59.443 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
KEITH CERNY: I do,
unfortunately, because,
there's been no improvement.

52:59.543 --> 53:01.412 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's been static for 25 years.

53:01.512 --> 53:03.414 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I think it is starting to
improve, slowly.

53:03.514 --> 53:08.185 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: From Dallas, I'm
Jeffrey Brown
for the "PBS NewsHour."

53:08.285 --> 53:11.989 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, you know
what I think.

53:12.089 --> 53:13.624 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We need more women conductors.

53:13.724 --> 53:15.292 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Said the maestra
of news.

53:15.392 --> 53:16.293 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

53:16.393 --> 53:17.294 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MILES O'BRIEN: All right.

53:17.394 --> 53:18.295 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
I agree.

53:18.395 --> 53:19.296 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's it for the "NewsHour"
tonight.

